# Protected paths — deleting any file matching these patterns must be DELIBERATE and DOCUMENTED.
#
# Why this file exists: account/social-login code (TIE-inherited AuthContext, SocialSignIn,
# useProtectedRoute) was deleted bundled inside an unrelated "brand: replace logo" commit
# (d98c38b) with zero mention. A whole capability vanished and nobody decided it. This guard
# makes that class of accident un-mergeable.
#
# How it works (scripts/guard_protected_deletions.py, enforced in CI):
#   - Each non-comment line is a Python regex matched against deleted file paths (vs the PR base).
#   - If a protected file is deleted, the PR FAILS unless a commit in the range carries a
#     `Removes:` trailer in its message acknowledging the removal and why.
#   - i.e. you CAN still remove these — you just can't do it silently or by accident.
#
# Keep this list in sync as the system grows (esp. when accounts/social-login is restored —
# add its context/components/hooks/endpoints here).

# ── Money rail (founder fence) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
^store_platform/src/Store\.Api/Payments/
^store_platform/src/Store\.Api/Endpoints/WebhookEndpoints\.cs$
^store_platform/src/Store\.Api/Endpoints/DeliveryEndpoints\.cs$

# ── Engine moat (verification / kill filter) ──────────────────────────────────
^verify\.py$
^kill_filter\.py$
^prompts/verdict\.md$

# ── Storefront critical surfaces ──────────────────────────────────────────────
^store_platform/src/Store\.Web/src/lib/api/client\.ts$

